This presidential memorandum delegates authority to the Secretary of Defense, in consultation with other government officials, to provide a report on the effects of cyber-enabled information operations on the national security of the United States to Congress. The memorandum also states that this delegation of authority applies to any future public law that is the same or similar to the referenced provision. The Secretary of Defense is instructed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register. The memorandum is signed by President Donald J. Trump.